\taxon{Definition}
\title{Bayesian Framework}
\p{Assume we have prior distributions #{(\pi_{0}, \pi_{1})} over the two hypotheses and there exists costs #{C_{1|0}}, #{C_{0|1}} associated with [type I and type II error](006B) respectively. Then the Bayes optimal solution is the solution of 
##{ \operatorname*{min}_{P_{Z|X}}\pi_{0}C_{1|0}\mathbb{P}_{H_{0}}(Z=1)+\pi_{1}C_{0|1}\mathbb{P}_{H_{1}}(Z=0). }
}
